      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 34
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_18_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_18",
      "description": "This 997.1 Carrera S is a driver-focused example featuring the 3.8L M97 flat-six powerplant and a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. The naturally aspirated engine delivers exceptional throttle response, supported by a proactive maintenance history including an IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh Rear Main Seal. Handling is sharpened by Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) and a limited-slip differential, providing superior mechanical grip and chassis composure through high-speed transitions. The braking system utilizes four-piston aluminum monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors for consistent thermal management. While exhibiting minor cosmetic patina consistent with a well-driven enthusiast vehicle, the mechanical vitals\u2014including cylinder bore scoping and compression numbers\u2014remain within optimal factory tolerances. It sits on staggered 19-inch 'Lobster Fork' alloys wrapped in high-performance rubber.",
